# Base URL of the FastAPI backend. No runtime default: if this is unset, the
# site never fires a request and simply serves the bundled saved result (the
# live-run button hides). Uncomment for local dev; in production point it at
# your deployed API (see DEPLOY.md).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Must match the backend's API_SECRET exactly (see root .env.example).
# Deliberately NOT prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_: it's read only by the server-side
# proxy at app/api/analyze/route.js, which attaches it as the x-api-secret
# header when forwarding to the backend. The browser never sees this value.
# If it doesn't match, every fresh run fails with 403 (surfaced as a distinct
# "auth" error after a click, never on page load). Only needed if the backend
# has ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set, i.e. fresh runs are enabled at all.
# API_SECRET=
